# Adding New Features — Checklists

## New API Endpoint

1. Add Pydantic request/response models
2. Add route handler with `Depends(get_current_user)` + `Depends(get_database)`
3. Check ownership — verify the resource belongs to `current_user`
4. Apply rate limiting for sensitive or expensive operations
5. Log operations with `logger.info()`, errors with `logger.error()`
6. Use `APIError` / `create_error_response` for all errors — **never bare `HTTPException`**
7. Register router in `main.py` under `/api/v1/` prefix
8. If the endpoint is also in the legacy `/api/` prefix, add `include_in_schema=False`
9. Add API integration tests in `tests/test_api/` using `authed_client` (mocked user) or `authed_client_with_user` (real DB user) as appropriate
10. Add E2E mocked coverage in `api-validation.spec.ts` — add a test that mocks the endpoint and verifies the frontend renders its response without JS errors
11. If the endpoint returns 429, add a matching test in `rate-limit.spec.ts`

## Workflow start — duplicate detection (`POST /api/v1/workflow/start`)

Before changing how jobs are keyed or deduplicated:

1. **`api/workflow.py`** — `_find_duplicate_active_application` / `_fingerprint_job_content` / `_canonical_job_url`; `normalize_title_company_key` is **`utils/application_dedupe.py`** (imported where needed). Duplicate responses use **`RES_3002`** (409) and must **release** `workflow_creating:{user_id}` on that path.
2. **Fingerprint** — stored on `WorkflowSession.job_input_data["content_fingerprint"]` only when normalized text length **≥ 80** (constant `_MIN_JOB_CONTENT_FINGERPRINT_CHARS`). Do not weaken NFKC / zero-width stripping without re-checking extension vs paste dedupe.
3. **Post-start duplicate handling** — see `applypilot-core.mdc` § *Duplicate job after start* (`find_conflicting_job_application` in `utils/application_dedupe.py`, `_maybe_fail_duplicate_job_after_analyzer` in `workflows/job_application_workflow.py`, integrity handling in `api/workflow.py` `_update_job_application_with_final_state`).
4. **Tests** — extend `tests/test_api/test_workflow.py` and `tests/test_application_dedupe.py` as appropriate; **frontend** must handle `RES_3002` in `ui/src/pages/dashboard-new-application.ts`, `ui/src/shared/api.ts`, and the Chrome extension (`popup.js`, `service-worker.js`).
5. **Docs** — `applypilot-core.mdc` § `RES_3002` and § *Duplicate job after start*; `dashboard-home.mdc` § *Toast Deduplication — `notifyReady`* (`c:` / `f:` keys vs legacy bare `sessionId`).

## New Database Column

1. Add mapped column to the SQLAlchemy model in `models/database.py`
2. Create Alembic migration: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"`
3. Verify migration file naming: `{YYYYMMDD}_0001_{NNN}_{description}.py`
4. Update `to_dict()` method on the model
5. If the column is JSONB, add `flag_modified()` calls everywhere it is updated
6. If the column is a soft-delete timestamp, add an index and filter in all list queries

## New Agent (Workflow)

1. Create agent class in `agents/` following the standard structure
2. Add `process()` or equivalent async method with BYOK support
3. Add state fields in `workflows/state_schema.py`
4. Add node and edges in `workflows/job_application_workflow.py` — **any failure in the node must fail the workflow** per `applypilot-core.mdc` (workflow failure — route to error handling, no partial outputs on `failed`)
5. Add `flag_modified()` for the new JSONB result field in `_save_workflow_state`
6. Add agent timing tracking (`agent_durations`)
7. If the agent caches shared (non-user-specific) results, add stampede protection via `acquire_compute_lock()` / `release_compute_lock()` (see `agent-patterns.mdc`)
8. Add a `get_cached_*` / `cache_*` helper pair in `utils/cache.py` using versioned keys (`_get_my_cache_key()` with `CACHE_VERSION` prefix) and register required fields in `_CACHE_REQUIRED_FIELDS`
9. Add unit tests in `tests/test_agents/test_{agent_name}.py` — patch `agents.{module}.genai` or the LLM client directly; test success, LLM JSON parse failure (fallback), BYOK override, and empty-input edge cases

## New Standalone Agent (Career Tool or On-Demand)

1. Create agent class in `agents/`
2. Add `CRITICAL WRITING RULES` to agent prompt — **no bracket placeholders** (`[Your Name]`, `[Company]`, etc.); use first name only for greetings, `Best regards,` close without sender name (see `career-tools.mdc`)
3. If the tool outputs an email, split into separate `subject` and `body` JSON fields — never a single `template` string
4. Add API endpoint in `api/tools.py` (career tools) or a dedicated router
5. Add rate limiting (recommended: 10/hour for tools, 5/hour for expensive ops)
6. Register router in `main.py`
7. Add frontend form/tab to `ui/dashboard/tools.html` following the sectioned card layout (`.salary-content-section` / `.salary-section-title` pattern)
8. For email outputs: add a copy button using `data-action="copyXxx"` that calls `_clipboardWrite(subject + '\n\n' + body)` — never `navigator.clipboard` directly
9. For large text inputs (>1000 chars): add `maxlength` + live `.char-counter` element (see `career-tools.mdc`)
10. Add unit tests in `tests/test_agents/test_{tool_name}.py` (mock the LLM client)
11. Add API integration tests in `tests/test_api/test_career_tools.py` using `authed_client`
12. Add E2E coverage in `e2e/tests/dashboard-pages.spec.ts` — form field visibility, input fillability, tab switching; mock the API and verify 200/429 responses do not crash the page (add matching test in `rate-limit.spec.ts`)

**Application-detail on-demand tabs** (Interview Prep, CV Optimizer, Practice Interview, Hiring Outreach pattern): also update **`mock-interview-feature.mdc` / `interview-prep-feature.mdc` / `cv-optimizer-feature.mdc` / `hiring-outreach-feature.mdc`** as appropriate; **`ui-application-detail.mdc`** tab count; **`USER_GUIDE.md`**, **`ui/help.html`**, **`README.md`**; indexes in **`CLAUDE.md`** / **`.cursorrules`**; **`e2e-testing.mdc`** / **`e2e/README.md`** tab count; **`CHANGELOG.md`**. If using LLM streaming, document in **`llm-integration.mdc`** + **`websocket-patterns.mdc`**.

## New Content Regeneration Endpoint

1. `POST /api/v1/workflow/regenerate-{name}/{session_id}`
2. Validate session ownership
3. Load existing state from DB
4. Re-invoke the target agent with existing state
5. Save with `flag_modified()` on the relevant JSONB field
6. Rate limit: 5/hour per user
7. Add regenerate button to `application.html` and wire to re-render function

## Adding a New Field to an Existing Agent Result

When adding a new field to an agent (e.g. `CompanyResearchResult`, `ProfileMatchingResult`):

1. Add the field to the dataclass in `workflows/state_schema.py` with an appropriate default
2. Update the agent prompt in `agents/*.py` to instruct the LLM to populate it
3. Map it in the agent's `_map_to_result()` method (if one exists)
4. Render it in `ui/src/application-detail/` (e.g. `render-*.ts`) inside the appropriate render function
5. Add CSS for any new UI components in `ui/dashboard/application.html`
6. Update `ui-application-detail.mdc` to document the new field and its CSS classes

## Adding a New Tab Section to application.html

1. Add the HTML section within the correct `#pane-*` container
2. Render data in `renderMainContent()` or the appropriate render function
3. Always use `escapeHtml()` for all LLM-generated strings
4. Always use `ensureArray()` for any field that could be null, undefined, or an object
5. Add CSS classes in `application.html` — use CSS variables, no inline colors
6. Update `ui-application-detail.mdc` with the new field mapping and CSS class list

